The CQL generator should be treated as a reasoning/planning node inside LangGraph — not as a tool and not as a separate autonomous agent.

This is the ideal architecture:

Component	Type

CQL Generator	LLM Node
Search	Tool
Fetch	Tool
Reranker	LLM Node
Traversal logic	Graph logic
Final synthesis	LLM Node



---

Why CQL Generator Should Be an LLM Node

Because it performs:

Natural Language
        ↓
Structured Retrieval Intent
        ↓
Valid CQL

This is reasoning + transformation.

It is NOT:

external side effect

API execution

deterministic utility


So it belongs inside:

planner node

structured output node



---

Recommended CQL Generator Architecture

Do NOT directly ask:

Generate CQL from this query

That becomes:

unsafe

unstable

hallucination-prone



---

Instead Use a 2-Step Design

STEP 1 — Retrieval Intent Extraction

LLM extracts structured intent.


---

